			<name>Shell Pernis Refinery &amp; Chemicals Complex</name>
			<description>Refinery: Shell Pernis Refinery &amp; Chemicals Complex
Classification: Mega-refinery
Location: Pernis, Port of Rotterdam, Netherlands
Owner: Shell Nederland Raffinaderij B.V., part of Shell plc
Capacity: Approximately 404,000 barrels per day
Main feedstocks: Imported crude oils and intermediate refinery streams delivered through Rotterdam’s marine terminals and pipeline network
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, LPG, naphtha, fuel oil, lubricants and chemical feedstocks
Markets: Netherlands, Germany, Belgium and other Northwest European markets
Recent data: A major crude-distillation unit of about 200,000 b/d was briefly shut and restarted in April 2026 following an unplanned operational issue. Shell also cancelled its separate Rotterdam biofuels project in 2025, recording total impairments and provisions of about $1.4 billion.
Strategic role: Europe’s largest integrated refinery and chemicals manufacturing site, with more than 60 production units and a key role in supplying fuels to the Netherlands and neighbouring countries.
Risks: Refinery-unit outages, Rotterdam port congestion, Rhine logistics disruption, high European energy and carbon costs, stricter environmental rules and pressure on European refining margins</description>
