			<name>Dangote Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: Dangote Petroleum Refinery
Location: Lekki Free Trade Zone, Lagos, Nigeria
Owner: Dangote Industries Limited
Capacity: 650,000 b/d nominal; performance tests indicated up to approximately 700,000 b/d in 2026
Feedstocks: Mainly Nigerian crude, supplemented by imported crude when required
Products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, LPG, naphtha and other refined products
Markets: Nigeria, West and East Africa, Europe and selected international markets
Recent data: Increased gasoline exports to African countries and became a major middle-distillate and jet-fuel supplier during the 2026 supply disruptions
Strategic role: Africa’s largest refinery and a major alternative source of refined products outside the Strait of Hormuz
Risks: Crude-supply constraints, unit outages, logistics bottlenecks, regulatory disputes and exposure to volatile refining margins</description>
