		<Placemark>
			<name>ExxonMobil Beaumont Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: ExxonMobil Beaumont Refinery
Classification: Mega-refinery
Location: Beaumont, Texas, United States
Owner: ExxonMobil
Capacity: About 609,000 barrels per calendar day; ExxonMobil has also described total capacity as approximately 630,000 b/d following the expansion
Main feedstocks: Primarily light crude from the Permian Basin, supplemented by other domestic and imported crude grades
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, LPG, petrochemical feedstocks and other refined products
Markets: Mainly the United States, particularly the Gulf Coast and inland markets, with access to international exports through Gulf Coast terminals
Recent data: A $2 billion expansion started up in 2023, adding around 250,000 b/d of crude-processing capacity—the largest U.S. refinery expansion in more than a decade
Strategic role: One of the three largest U.S. refineries and a highly integrated refining and petrochemical complex, closely linked to ExxonMobil’s growing Permian production
Risks: Gulf Coast hurricanes, flooding, refinery outages, pipeline or marine-logistics disruptions, environmental regulation and volatile refining margins</description>
