			<name>Marathon Garyville Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: Marathon Garyville Refinery
Classification: Mega-refinery
Location: Garyville, Louisiana, United States
Owner: Marathon Petroleum Corporation
Capacity: 617,000 barrels per calendar day
Main feedstocks: Broad crude slate, including domestic U.S. and imported light, medium and heavy crude grades
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, natural gas liquids, petrochemical feedstocks, heavy fuel oil, asphalt and propane
Markets: U.S. Gulf Coast, domestic inland markets and international export markets via pipeline, barge, rail, truck and ocean tanker
Recent data: In 2025, the refinery completed a major steam-efficiency initiative that exceeded its target and reduced energy use and emissions; Marathon also disclosed new Garyville optimization investments in its 2025 annual report
Strategic role: One of the largest and most flexible refineries in the United States, with direct access to the Mississippi River and multiple export channels
Risks: Gulf Coast hurricanes, Mississippi River logistics disruption, refinery outages, flooding, environmental regulation and volatile refining margins</description>
