			<name>HD Hyundai Oilbank Daesan Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: HD Hyundai Oilbank Daesan Refinery
Classification: Mega-refinery
Location: Daesan Industrial Complex, Seosan, South Korea
Owner: HD Hyundai Oilbank, part of the HD Hyundai group
Capacity: Approximately 520,000 barrels per day of crude-oil refining capacity
Main feedstocks: Imported Middle Eastern crude, condensate and other light-to-heavy crude grades
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, naphtha, LPG, marine fuel, lubricants and petrochemical feedstocks
Markets: South Korea and export markets across Northeast and Southeast Asia
Recent data: A 130,000-tonne-per-year biodiesel plant began operating at Daesan in 2024, supporting the group’s expansion into lower-carbon fuels.
Recent development: In 2026, South Korea approved a major restructuring of the Daesan petrochemical complex involving HD Hyundai Oilbank, HD Hyundai Chemical and Lotte Chemical, aimed at reducing overcapacity and integrating refining and petrochemical operations.
Strategic role: One of South Korea’s major export-oriented refining and petrochemical hubs, with strong integration between fuel production, base oils and chemicals
Risks: Dependence on imported crude, Strait of Hormuz and Asian shipping disruptions, weak petrochemical margins, regional overcapacity, refinery outages and environmental regulation</description>
