			<name>Ras Tanura Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: Ras Tanura Refinery
Classification: Mega-refinery
Location: Ras Tanura, Eastern Province, Saudi Arabia
Owner: Saudi Aramco
Capacity: Approximately 550,000 barrels per day, making it Saudi Arabia’s largest refinery.
Main feedstocks: Primarily Saudi crude oils and condensates supplied from the Kingdom’s eastern production system
Main products: LPG, naphtha, gasoline, jet fuel/kerosene, diesel, heavy fuel oil and asphalt.
Markets: Saudi domestic demand and international export markets, especially Asia, through the adjacent Ras Tanura marine terminal
Recent data: The refinery was shut as a precaution after a drone strike on 2 March 2026 and restarted on 13 March 2026. Crude loadings at the Ras Tanura terminal later resumed in June 2026 after a prolonged disruption.
Strategic role: Saudi Arabia’s largest and one of its most complex refineries, integrated with one of the world’s most important crude-oil export terminals
Risks: Strait of Hormuz disruption, drone or missile attacks, regional conflict, terminal shutdowns, imported equipment constraints, refinery outages and shipping-security costs</description>
