		<Placemark id="03CB070FB93EB406A8C4">
			<name>Ruwais Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: Ruwais Refinery
Classification: Mega-refinery
Location: Al Ruwais Industrial City, Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates
Owner: ADNOC Refining, part of the ADNOC Group
Capacity: More than 922,000 barrels per stream day, making it one of the world’s largest refining complexes.
Main feedstocks: Abu Dhabi crude and condensate, including Upper Zakum; the crude-flexibility project is designed to process more than 50 crude grades
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, naphtha, LPG, fuel oil and petrochemical feedstocks
Markets: UAE domestic demand and international markets, particularly Asia
Recent data: In 2026, regional conflict disrupted Strait of Hormuz shipping and temporarily affected Ruwais exports. ADNOC resumed naphtha exports through Sohar, Oman, using ship-to-ship transfers to bypass the strait.
Strategic role: ADNOC’s main downstream hub, integrating refining, petrochemicals, fertilizers, industrial gases and export infrastructure
Risks: Strait of Hormuz closure, drone or missile attacks, regional conflict, marine-export disruption, refinery outages and dependence on Asian petrochemical demand</description>
