			<name>Port Arthur Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: Motiva Port Arthur Refinery
Classification: Mega-refinery
Location: Port Arthur, Texas, United States
Owner: Motiva Enterprises, wholly owned by Saudi Aramco
Capacity: About 640,500 b/d of crude capacity; Motiva reports approximately 730,000 b/d of total throughput for the wider manufacturing complex
Main feedstocks: Highly flexible crude slate; capable of processing more than 100 crude grades, including domestic and imported light, medium and heavy oils
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, base oils, LPG and petrochemical feedstocks
Markets: Primarily the United States and the Americas, with access to international export markets through the Gulf Coast
Recent data: In March 2026, an operational upset at the integrated chemical plant caused flaring, although the refinery remained identified as the largest in the United States by crude capacity
Strategic role: North America’s largest single-site refinery and home to the largest base-oil plant in the Western Hemisphere
Risks: Gulf Coast hurricanes, flooding, industrial outages, marine and pipeline disruptions, environmental constraints and volatile refining margins</description>
