			<name>Al Zour Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: Al-Zour Refinery
Classification: Mega-refinery
Location: Al-Zour, southern Kuwait
Owner: Kuwait Integrated Petroleum Industries Company (KIPIC), a subsidiary of Kuwait Petroleum Corporation (KPC)
Capacity: 615,000 barrels per day nominal; actual average processing reached about 507,000 b/d in fiscal year 2024/2025
Main feedstocks: Kuwait Export Crude, medium and heavy Kuwaiti crude, including Kuwait Heavy Crude
Main products: Very-low-sulfur fuel oil, diesel, jet fuel, naphtha, LPG, sulfur and other clean petroleum products
Markets: Kuwait’s domestic power sector and international markets, especially Southeast Asia and Middle Eastern bunkering hubs; diesel and jet-fuel cargoes have also reached Europe and Africa
Recent data: In January 2026, VLSFO exports exceeded 1 million tonnes, or about 205,000 b/d, a monthly record after the refinery recovered from an outage; roughly 70% of those volumes were headed to Southeast Asia.
Strategic role: One of the world’s largest newly built refineries, designed to process heavy Kuwaiti crude and supply both low-sulfur fuel to domestic power plants and cleaner export products.
Risks: Strait of Hormuz disruption, regional conflict, unit outages, heavy-crude processing difficulties, export-terminal disruption and dependence on Asian fuel-oil demand</description>
