		<Placemark id="046FC8A6A83EB3FF24A7">
			<name> SK Energy Ulsan Complex</name>
			<description>Refinery: SK Energy Ulsan Complex
Classification: Super-refinery / Mega-refinery
Location: Ulsan, South Korea
Owner: SK Energy, part of SK Innovation
Capacity: Approximately 840,000 barrels per day of crude-distillation capacity
Main feedstocks: Imported Middle Eastern crude, condensates and other light-to-heavy grades
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, naphtha, LPG, marine fuels, lubricants and petrochemical feedstocks
Markets: South Korea and export markets across Northeast and Southeast Asia
Recent data: In 2025, SK Energy carried out maintenance on crude-distillation and residue-desulfurization units while maintaining exports through higher utilization of the remaining units
Strategic role: South Korea’s largest refinery and one of Asia’s biggest integrated refining and petrochemical complexes
Risks: Dependence on imported crude, Strait of Hormuz and Malacca disruptions, refinery outages, weak Asian refining and petrochemical margins, and regional overcapacity</description>
