		<Placemark id="004987E8B03FA09C66A7">
			<name>Shell Energy and Chemicals Park Rheinland</name>
			<description>Refinery: Shell Energy and Chemicals Park Rheinland
Classification: Large refinery / transitioning energy-and-chemicals complex — not currently a mega-refinery
Location: Godorf and Wesseling, near Cologne, Germany
Owner: Shell Deutschland GmbH, part of Shell plc
Current refining status: The complex historically processed about 340,000 b/d, but crude-oil processing at Wesseling ended in 2025. Crude refining continues at Godorf, historically accounting for roughly 190,000 b/d.
Main feedstocks: Imported crude oil at Godorf; Wesseling is being repurposed toward lower-carbon and specialty products
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, heating oil, petrochemical feedstocks, hydrogen and, increasingly, high-quality lubricant base oils
Markets: Germany and neighbouring Northwest European markets, especially the Rhine-Ruhr industrial region
Recent data: Shell is converting the Wesseling hydrocracker into a 300,000-tonne-per-year Group III base-oil plant, expected to be Germany’s largest when completed in 2028.
Strategic role: Major Rhine-region fuel and chemicals hub undergoing conversion from conventional refining toward hydrogen, bio-LNG, specialty base oils and lower-carbon energy products
Risks: European refining-margin pressure, high energy and carbon costs, Rhine logistics disruption, transition-project delays and declining regional fossil-fuel demand</description>
