		<Placemark id="0D1FFEB8F33FCC6A863D">
			<name>Gunvor Raffinerie Ingolstadt</name>
			<description>Refinery: Gunvor Refinery Ingolstadt
Location: Kösching/Ingolstadt, Bavaria, Germany
Owner: Gunvor Group, through Gunvor Raffinerie Ingolstadt GmbH
Capacity: Approximately 110,000 barrels per day
Main feedstocks: Imported crude delivered mainly through the Transalpine Pipeline from Trieste
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, heating oil, bitumen, LPG and other middle distillates
Markets: Bavaria, southern Germany and parts of Austria
Recent data: Gunvor reported a sharp decline in group profit in 2025, while continuing to operate Ingolstadt as one of its core refining assets; no major recent capacity expansion has been announced for the site.
Strategic role: Important inland refinery supplying the landlocked southern German market and connected to Mediterranean crude imports through the TAL pipeline
Risks: TAL pipeline disruption, refinery outages, high European energy and carbon costs, weak refining margins and declining regional fossil-fuel demand</description>
