		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="06F4988BF93EB78E9536">
			<name> Slovnaft Bratislava Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: Slovnaft Bratislava Refinery
Classification: Conventional refinery — not a mega-refinery
Location: Bratislava, Slovakia
Owner: Slovnaft a.s., part of MOL Group
Capacity: Approximately 124,000 barrels per day, or about 6.1 million tonnes per year
Main feedstocks: Traditionally Russian Urals crude through the southern Druzhba pipeline, with increasing use of alternative grades supplied through the Adria pipeline and MOL’s regional network
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, LPG, heating oil, bitumen, sulfur and petrochemical feedstocks
Markets: Slovakia and neighbouring Central European markets, especially the Czech Republic, Austria, Hungary and Poland
Recent data: Slovnaft has increased processing of non-Russian crude, but diversification remains constrained by Adria pipeline availability and refinery adaptation. In 2025, a shortfall in an Arab Light delivery highlighted these logistical limitations.
Strategic role: Slovakia’s only refinery and one of Central Europe’s most complex refining-petrochemical sites, with a Nelson Complexity Index of about 11.5
Risks: Druzhba supply disruption, dependence on Russian crude, Adria pipeline constraints, sanctions, inland logistics, refinery outages and high European energy and carbon costs</description>
