		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="08C5BE10003EB7937597">
			<name>ORLEN Unipetrol Kralupy Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: ORLEN Unipetrol Kralupy Refinery
Classification: Conventional refinery — not a mega-refinery
Location: Kralupy nad Vltavou, Central Bohemian Region, Czech Republic
Owner: ORLEN Unipetrol, part of Poland’s ORLEN Group
Capacity: Approximately 3.3 million tonnes per year, equivalent to roughly 65,000–70,000 barrels per day
Main feedstocks: Mainly light, low-sulfur crude oils from Azerbaijan, Kazakhstan and Algeria, delivered from Trieste through the TAL and IKL pipeline systems.
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, LPG, jet-fuel components, sulfur and petrochemical feedstocks
Markets: Primarily the Czech domestic market and neighbouring Central European countries
Recent data: The refinery completed a major planned turnaround and modernization in spring 2026, restarting operations in May after more than one month of maintenance.
Strategic role: Important Czech conversion refinery with an FCC unit, supporting the country’s transition away from Russian crude supply
Risks: TAL/IKL pipeline disruption, inland logistics constraints, power outages, maintenance shutdowns, refinery-unit failures and high European energy and carbon costs</description>
			<LookAt>
