		<Placemark id="06D0FD3EF93F39E6DA67">
			<name>Baizan Oil Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: Bazian Oil Refinery
Classification: Conventional refinery — not a mega-refinery
Location: Bazian industrial area, approximately 25 km west of Sulaymaniyah, Kurdistan Region of Iraq
Owner/Operator: Qaiwan Group, historically associated with Bezhan Petrochemical
Capacity: Approximately 40,000–45,000 barrels per day
Main feedstocks: Regional crude oils produced in northern Iraq and the Kurdistan Region
Main products: Diesel, gasoline, kerosene, naphtha, fuel oil and other petroleum products
Markets: Mainly the Kurdistan Region and northern Iraqi domestic market
Recent development: Previous expansion projects added gasoline-processing, pre-flash, LPG loading and unloading, and supporting refinery infrastructure
Strategic role: One of the Kurdistan Region’s main privately operated refineries, supporting local fuel supply and reducing dependence on imported refined products
Risks: Regional political instability, crude-supply disruption, infrastructure constraints, refinery outages, fuel-quality regulation and dependence on the local market</description>
