		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="0F644673683F3A113A18">
			<name>Baniyas Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: Baniyas Refinery
Classification: Conventional refinery — not a mega-refinery
Location: Baniyas, Tartus Governorate, Mediterranean coast of Syria
Owner/Operator: Syrian state petroleum sector; historically operated by the Baniyas Refinery Company and now associated with the Syrian Petroleum Company
Nominal capacity: Approximately 125,000–130,000 barrels per day
Recent effective capacity: Around 95,000 b/d was reported in late 2025 because of degraded and ageing facilities. After maintenance, the refinery reportedly resumed full production in May 2026.
Main feedstocks: Syrian light and heavy crude oils from northeastern fields, supplemented by imported crude. The refinery historically depended heavily on Iranian supply, while more recent deliveries have included Saudi crude and domestic Syrian production.
Main products: Gasoline, diesel/gas oil, kerosene, LPG, naphtha, fuel oil, bitumen and other petroleum products
Configuration: Four principal refining trains, including units designed for both lighter Euphrates crude and heavier Syrian crude grades
Logistics: Directly connected to the Baniyas Mediterranean oil terminal and historically linked by pipelines to Syrian producing regions. The terminal is also being developed as an alternative transit and export route for Iraqi crude, fuel oil and naphtha.
Markets: Primarily Syria’s domestic fuel market, with growing potential for regional transit and re-export activities
Strategic role: Syria’s largest refinery and a central element of the country’s fuel security and post-war petroleum-sector reconstruction
Risks: Ageing infrastructure, uncertain crude availability, pipeline damage, maintenance shortages, sanctions legacy, power interruptions, coastal oil spills and regional security instability</description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>35.95942709999999</longitude>
				<latitude>35.2162342</latitude>
				<altitude>0</altitude>
				<heading>0</heading>
				<tilt>0</tilt>
				<gx:fovy>35</gx:fovy>
