			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="06F5B7E64C3F7F2F037B">
			<name>TotalEnergies Normandy Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: TotalEnergies Normandy Refinery
Classification: Large refinery — not a mega-refinery
Location: Gonfreville-l’Orcher, near Le Havre, Normandy, France
Owner/Operator: TotalEnergies
Capacity: Approximately 240,000 barrels per day, equivalent to nearly 12 million tonnes of crude oil per year.
Main feedstocks: Imported crude oils delivered through the Port of Le Havre and the lower-Seine petroleum logistics network
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, LPG, heating oil, fuel oil, base petrochemical feedstocks and sustainable aviation fuel
Petrochemical integration: The refinery is integrated with a major petrochemical complex producing olefins, polymers and other chemical intermediates
Markets: France and other European and international markets; TotalEnergies states that products from the Normandy platform are shipped to around 60 countries.
Recent development: The site began producing sustainable aviation fuel through co-processing and remains one of TotalEnergies’ principal European refining and petrochemical platforms.
Strategic role: France’s largest refinery and a critical supplier of fuels to northern France, the Paris region and international markets. It represents around 12% of French refining capacity.
Risks: Refinery-unit outages, labour strikes, Seine and Le Havre logistics disruptions, high European energy and carbon costs, environmental constraints and declining long-term demand for fossil fuels</description>
