		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="0F4EF174E33F7FC8FF41">
			<name>Valero Pembroke Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: Valero Pembroke Refinery
Classification: Large refinery — near mega-refinery threshold
Location: Rhoscrowther, near Pembroke, Pembrokeshire, Wales, United Kingdom
Owner/Operator: Valero Energy
Total throughput capacity: Approximately 270,000 barrels per day, comprising about 220,000 b/d of crude oil and 50,000 b/d of other feedstocks.
Main feedstocks: Imported crude oils and intermediate feedstocks delivered through the Milford Haven deep-water marine and storage network
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, heating oil and low-sulfur fuel oil.
Markets: Primarily the United Kingdom and Ireland, with access to wider Atlantic and Northwest European markets
Complexity: Highly complex conversion refinery, with a reported Nelson Complexity Index of approximately 11.8.
Energy integration: A cogeneration unit supplies electricity and steam to the refinery, improving energy efficiency and operating reliability.
Strategic role: One of Western Europe’s largest and most complex refineries and one of the United Kingdom’s four remaining major operating refineries in 2026.
Risks: Milford Haven marine disruption, refinery-unit outages, labour or maintenance interruptions, high UK energy and carbon costs, environmental regulation and weak European refining margins</description>
