		<Placemark id="0F229C480B3FCC0E95ED">
			<name>VAROPreem Cressier Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: VAROPreem – VARO Refining Cressier SA
Location: Cressier, Canton of Neuchâtel, Switzerland
Owner: VAROPreem, through VARO Refining Cressier SA; the site is fully owned by the group.
Capacity: Approximately 68,000–70,000 barrels per day of refined products.
Main feedstocks: Imported crude delivered from Fos-sur-Mer through the South European Pipeline system and onward pipeline connections to Switzerland
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, heating oil, jet-fuel components, LPG, bitumen and other middle distillates
Markets: Primarily Switzerland; the refinery supplies approximately 30% of the Swiss fuel market.
Recent data: The site operates an approximately 8 MW solar facility, producing around 8.4 GWh annually, and supplies residual heat to a district-heating network serving more than 5,000 nearby households.
Strategic role: Switzerland’s only operating conventional refinery and critical national energy-supply infrastructure.
Risks: Dependence on the Fos-sur-Mer and pipeline supply chain, Alpine and inland logistics constraints, refinery outages, high Swiss and European energy costs, carbon regulation and declining fossil-fuel demand</description>
