		<Placemark id="08F5E005523EB856C896">
			<name>Vopak Terminal Vlaardingen</name>
			<description>Terminal: Vopak Terminal Vlaardingen
Classification: Major independent liquid-bulk storage terminal / biofuels and specialty-products hub
Location: Koningin Wilhelminahaven, Vlaardingen, Port of Rotterdam, Netherlands
Owner/Operator: Royal Vopak
Main commodities: Vegetable oils, animal fats, biodiesel, methyl esters, oleochemicals, base oils, sustainable feedstocks and selected liquid chemicals
Storage capacity: Approximately 564,000–600,000 m³. The terminal has around 292 tanks, ranging from about 250 to 6,240 m³.
Berths / draught: 3 berths for seagoing vessels, 10 barge berths, with a maximum draught of about 13 metres
Transport access: Seagoing vessels, inland barges, rail tank cars and road tankers
Main services: Storage, blending, heating, weighing, nitrogen blanketing and dedicated handling systems
Main markets: Rotterdam–Antwerp–Amsterdam trading area and wider European markets
Recent development: In 2023, Vopak commissioned 16 new tanks totalling 64,000 m³ for waste-based feedstocks used in biodiesel, renewable diesel and sustainable aviation fuel production.
Strategic role: Major European hub for biofuel feedstocks, vegetable oils, base oils and specialty liquid products, with strong multimodal access
Risks: Fire and contamination risk, Rhine and port-logistics disruption, product segregation requirements, environmental regulation and dependence on European biofuel demand</description>
