	<Folder>
		<name>Ports, aviation, defense (fuel demand sites)</name>
		<Placemark id="02F63AE6E93FCA0C0978">
			<name>Port of Moerdijk – Industrial &amp; Logistics Zone</name>
			<description>Hub: Port of Moerdijk – Industrial &amp; Logistics Zone
Classification: Major industrial, chemical and multimodal logistics hub
Location: Moerdijk, North Brabant, Netherlands, between Rotterdam and Antwerp
Owner/Operator: Port of Moerdijk Authority
Area: Approximately 2,635 hectares under port management
Companies: More than 400 companies, active in chemicals, energy, manufacturing, recycling, terminals, warehousing and distribution
Main activities: Petrochemicals, chemical production, liquid and dry bulk handling, container logistics, warehousing, recycling, energy services and value-added distribution
Cargo handled: Containers, chemicals, petroleum products, biofuels, industrial raw materials, dry bulk, project cargo and general cargo
Connectivity: Direct access to deep-sea and inland shipping, rail, pipelines and the A16/A17 motorway network; strategically positioned on the Rotterdam–Antwerp corridor
Industrial integration: Part of the wider Rotterdam–Moerdijk chemical cluster, with pipeline links toward Rotterdam, Antwerp, Zeeland, Limburg and the Ruhr industrial region
Logistics expansion: The adjacent Logistics Park Moerdijk is being developed for large-scale storage, distribution and value-added logistics, with phased completion planned through 2030.
Strategic role: The port is officially described as the Netherlands’ fourth seaport of national importance and its second-largest container port. It serves as a major hinterland gateway between the North Sea ports and continental Europe.
Energy-transition role: Moerdijk is developing circular chemistry, recycling, bio-based feedstocks, hydrogen infrastructure and industrial symbiosis, with land reserved for circular and chemical activities.
Risks: Chemical and fire hazards, hazardous-goods incidents, Rhine–Meuse waterway disruption, rail or motorway congestion, pipeline outages, environmental permitting constraints and exposure to European industrial demand</description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>4.6062531</longitude>
				<latitude>51.6745104</latitude>
				<altitude>0</altitude>
				<heading>0</heading>
				<tilt>0</tilt>
				<gx:fovy>35</gx:fovy>
				<range>1476.039435460105</range>
				<altitudeMode>relativeToGround</altitudeMode>
