	<Folder>
		<name>Renewable Fuels &amp; Low-Carbon Production Sites</name>
		<Placemark id="0E467C7C173FCEB24E88">
			<name>VAROPreem Lysekil Refinery &amp; Renewable Fuels Hub</name>
			<description>Refinery: VAROPreem Lysekil Refinery &amp; Renewable Fuels Hub
Classification: Large refinery and renewable-fuels production site
Location: Lysekil, Västra Götaland County, Sweden
Owner: VAROPreem
Capacity: Approximately 220,000 barrels per day of conventional refining capacity
Renewable capacity: Up to 900,000 m³/year from the upgraded Synsat unit; total Lysekil renewable capacity exceeds 1 million m³/year
Main feedstocks: Imported crude oils and renewable raw materials such as tall oil, used cooking oils, animal fats and pyrolysis oils
Main products: Diesel, gasoline, LPG, HVO renewable diesel and other co-processed renewable fuels
Markets: Sweden, Norway and other Northwest European markets
Recent data: The Synsat upgrade entered service in 2025, allowing up to 40% renewable material to be co-processed with diesel
Strategic role: Major Nordic refinery and large-scale renewable-fuels hub supporting the decarbonisation of road, marine, aviation and industrial transport
Risks: Seaborne-feedstock dependence, refinery outages, North Sea weather, high energy and carbon costs, and uncertainty over future fuel demand</description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>11.4172029</longitude>
				<latitude>58.3484121</latitude>
				<altitude>0</altitude>
				<heading>0</heading>
				<tilt>0</tilt>
				<gx:fovy>35</gx:fovy>
				<range>1219.33616712355</range>
				<altitudeMode>relativeToGround</altitudeMode>
			</LookAt>
			<styleUrl>#msn_ranger_station</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<altitudeMode>relativeToGround</altitudeMode>
				<coordinates>11.4172029,58.3484121,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="01AF5FA0193FCEBB0A64">
			<name>VAROPreem Gothenburg Refinery &amp; Renewable Fuels Hub</name>
			<description>Refinery: VAROPreem Gothenburg Refinery &amp; Renewable Fuels Hub
Classification: Conventional refinery and renewable-fuels production site
Location: Hisingen, Gothenburg, Sweden
Owner: VAROPreem
Capacity: Approximately 132,000 barrels per day of total refining capacity
Renewable capacity: About 300,000–320,000 m³ per year, including HVO100 production
Main feedstocks: Imported crude oils and renewable raw materials such as tall oil, used cooking oils, animal fats and other industrial or food-sector by-products
Main products: Diesel, gasoline, LPG, HVO100 renewable diesel and other co-processed renewable fuels
Markets: Sweden and other Northwest European markets, including exports of HVO100 to the Netherlands
Recent data: Production has reached about 900,000 litres of renewable fuel per day; the Gothenburg site can process 100% renewable feedstock in its converted hydroprocessing unit
Strategic role: One of Sweden’s principal renewable-fuels hubs and an early European pioneer in co-processing renewable feedstocks, which began at the site in 2010
Risks: Dependence on seaborne crude and renewable feedstocks, refinery outages, port disruption, feedstock-price volatility, sustainability requirements and changing European fuel policy</description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>11.8323886</longitude>
				<latitude>57.70834980000001</latitude>
				<altitude>0</altitude>
				<heading>0</heading>
				<tilt>0</tilt>
				<gx:fovy>35</gx:fovy>
				<range>1244.359535702669</range>
				<altitudeMode>relativeToGround</altitudeMode>
			</LookAt>
			<styleUrl>#msn_ranger_station</styleUrl>
			<Point>
