	<Folder>
		<name>Pipelines refined products</name>
		<Placemark id="0D7B0B4A7E3F6266D6D6">
			<name>NATO pipeline</name>
			<description>The Central Europe Pipeline System, or CEPS, is NATO’s largest fuel pipeline network. It connects ports, refineries, storage depots, military bases and major civil airports across France, Belgium, Luxembourg, Germany and the Netherlands. The system transports refined petroleum products—including jet fuel, diesel, gasoline and naphtha—but does not normally carry crude oil. Originally developed to secure military fuel supplies, it is also used for civilian distribution during peacetime. The CEPS remains operational and plays a strategic role in European fuel security and military logistics.</description>
