		<Placemark id="0CE1A26CAC402138B5D4">
			<name>Forties route</name>
			<description>Crude: Forties Blend
API: ~42.1°
Sulfur: ~0.56%
Type: Light, medium-sulfur North Sea crude
Origin: UK North Sea fields; transported through the Forties Pipeline System to Dalmeny and exported from Hound Point, Scotland
Markets: Mainly Northwest European refiners, including the United Kingdom, the Netherlands, Germany and France
Used for: Gasoline, naphtha, jet fuel, diesel, gasoil and petrochemical feedstocks
Pricing: One of the BFOET grades supporting Dated Brent; value is adjusted for sulfur quality through the North Sea sulfur de-escalator
Vessels: Typically Aframax or Suezmax; Hound Point can also accommodate VLCC cargoes above 2 million barrels
Transit: Around 2–4 days from Hound Point to Rotterdam through the North Sea
Risks: North Sea storms, Forties Pipeline System outages, Hound Point loading delays, variable sulfur quality and congestion near Rotterdam</description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>4.272428319770761</longitude>
				<latitude>52.00483012429128</latitude>
