		<Placemark id="0D1381C8C640213F3148">
			<name>Johan Sverdrup route</name>
			<description>Crude: Johan Sverdrup
API: ~28.0–28.7°
Sulfur: ~0.80–0.85%
Type: Medium, medium-sulfur North Sea crude
Origin: Johan Sverdrup Field, Norwegian North Sea; transported by a 274 km pipeline to Mongstad Terminal
Markets: Northwest Europe and Asia, including major demand from Chinese and other Asian refiners
Used for: Diesel, jet fuel, gasoil, fuel oil and other middle/heavy refinery products
Pricing: Assessed against Dated Brent; the differential varies with refining margins, freight and demand for medium-sour crude
Vessels: Typically Aframax or Suezmax tankers loaded at Mongstad Terminal
Transit: Around 3–5 days from Mongstad to Rotterdam
Risks: North Sea weather, pipeline or terminal outages, loading delays and congestion in the English Channel and Rotterdam approaches</description>
