		<Placemark>
			<name>Dalia crude route</name>
			<description>Crude: Dalia
API: 23.3–23.7°
Sulfur: 0.49–0.51%
Type: Heavy, sweet offshore crude
Origin: Dalia Field, Block 17, offshore Angola
Markets: Mainly China; also Spain, France and the Netherlands
Used for: Low-sulfur fuel oil, middle distillates and heavy refinery products
Pricing: Traded at a variable differential to Dated Brent; premium or discount depends on Asian demand, freight and refinery margins
Vessels: Loaded offshore from the Dalia FPSO, typically on Suezmax or VLCC tankers; Suezmax is suitable for Rotterdam
Transit: Approximately 17–21 days to Rotterdam
Risks: Offshore-loading delays, Atlantic weather, piracy risk in the Gulf of Guinea, and congestion in the English Channel and Dover Strait</description>
			<styleUrl>#msn_ylw-pushpin2</styleUrl>
