		<Placemark>
			<name>Hebron crude route</name>
			<description>Crude: Hebron
API: 20.4–21.2°
Sulfur: 0.79–0.80%
Type: Heavy, medium-sulfur crude
Markets: UK, Netherlands, Italy, China
Used for: Heavy products, fuel oil and middle distillates
Pricing: Variable discount to Dated Brent
Vessels: Ice-strengthened Aframax shuttle tanker, then Aframax/Suezmax to Rotterdam
Transit: 9–12 days
Risks: Icebergs, Atlantic storms, loading delays and Dover Strait congestion</description>
